&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About InnoPhase IoT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are keen to work with a bunch of brilliant people with various backgrounds, if you share the same value of working smart and celebrating successes, if you have enthusiasm for big technology in a small company, if your goals are to learn and experience different aspects of work--not just singing the same song every day, you’ll find your playground at Innophase IoT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people seeking AWESOMENESS! If you’re good at what you do, you can work anywhere. If you’re the best at what you do, come work at Innophase IoT!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Role Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design, implement, and ship Bluetooth Controller firmware across BLE (Link Layer/MAC) and Bluetooth Classic (BR/EDR LM behaviors) on our SoCs. Work spans bring-up, timing &amp;amp; reliability, test/qualification, and cross-functional debug with RF, systems, and QA—hands-on from lab benches to release.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Firmware development (Controller): Implement and maintain controller features aligned to Bluetooth Core Spec 5.x and 6.x for BLE and Bluetooth Classic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring-up &amp;amp; stabilization: Bring up features on FPGA/eval boards/silicon; tune timing/latency paths in RTOS environments for BLE and Classic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test &amp;amp; qualification support: support certification/interop; analyze sniffer/HCI logs and close issues with clear root cause.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;System-level debugging: Triage issues across firmware, drivers, and basic RF interactions; collaborate with Hardware/RF, Systems, and QA to land fixes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tooling &amp;amp; automation: Contribute HCI test scripts, utilities, and CI checks that improve repeatability and coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance: Participate in code reviews, documentation, and sustaining engineering for released features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Core Competencies&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience in Bluetooth controller firmware with understanding of BLE LL/MAC and Bluetooth Classic LM procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong embedded C skills (interrupts, memory-safe coding, RTOS concurrency).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with UART/SPI/I²C and board bring-up workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with sniffer/HCI logs (BLE and Classic) and embedded debuggers; strong analytical and troubleshooting ability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organized, detail-oriented, proactive, and effective in cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear written and verbal communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Qualifications (Requirements)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;E./B.Tech/M.E./M.Tech in ECE/EE/CS (or equivalent practical experience).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5–9 years of embedded firmware experience on MCUs/SoCs with RTOS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in C, version control, code reviews, and CI basics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing to Bluetooth Core Spec 5.x and 6.x at the controller level—covering BLE LL/MAC and exposure to Bluetooth Classic BR/EDR LM procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to system test, troubleshooting, and root-cause analysis of Bluetooth products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic RF awareness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coexistence basics (Wi‑Fi/Bluetooth) and lab tools (oscilloscope, logic analyzer, power meter).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with open Bluetooth ecosystems (e.g., Zephyr/NimBLE).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
