&lt;h2&gt;Role Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Firmware Engineer with deep expertise in Zigbee, Thread, and IEEE 802.15.4 wireless stacks. The candidate will focus on architecting, developing, and optimizing embedded wireless protocol stacks on resource-constrained platforms, ensuring compliance, performance, and reliability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect, design, and implement firmware solutions for Zigbee/Thread and IEEE 802.15.4-based products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and optimize low-level drivers, MAC/PHY interfaces, and protocol stack layers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debug and resolve wireless interoperability and certification issues using sniffers (Ubiqua, Wireshark, Perytons).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with hardware, QA, and product teams to ensure robust HW/SW co-design and regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debug, analyze, and optimize power consumption and timing for battery-operated IoT devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support certification and compliance efforts for Zigbee/Thread-based products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document software design, testing procedures, and release notes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Competencies&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of experience in embedded firmware development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong programming skills in C / Embedded C; assembly or scripting (Python) a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in IEEE 802.15.4 MAC/PHY, Zigbee, and Thread protocol stacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with embedded RTOS (FreeRTOS, Zephyr, or Linux system programming).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in debug tools (JTAG, GDB, oscilloscopes, logic analyzers, sniffers).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of microcontrollers, transceivers, and RF system design basics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on debugging and optimization for low-power wireless systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with IoT frameworks and domains like home automation, security, and energy management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem-solving, communication, and cross-functional collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Qualification&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
